But this assumption holding good, on which Euclid supports himself after 1. 28, it is manifest to all geometers that the hypothesis of right angle alone is true, nor any place left for the hypothesis of obtuse angle. Therefore the hypothesis of obtuse angle is absolutely false, because it destroys itself.
